<h4>How does SSStutterBuddy make money?</h4>
<p>
	That's the neat part. It doesn't.
</p>
<p>
	<b>SSStutterBuddy is free and will always be free.</b> SSStutterBuddy will neither charge researchers for posting studies, nor take a cut from the compensation given to study participants.
</p>
<p>
	Our mission is to help advance stuttering research. As such, we feel that any money earmarked for research should go either towards the PWS who participate in studies or the study itself, not a third-party application.
</p>
<h4>But building a web application is expensive. How will SSStutterBuddy do it without money?</h4>
<p>
	The most expensive part of creating a new web application is not buying the technology, it's paying the developers who write the code. SSStutterBuddy's founder, Tom Lovett, is a professional web developer who has donated personal time to build this project.
</p>
<p>
	If you would like to volunteer for the pokect, send an email to admin at ssstutterbuddy dot com. Technical skills are preferred, but anyone can help!
</p>
<p>
	SSStutterBuddy will accept donations to help defray the minor costs of hosting the website. Large donations will be put towards hiring professional talent to supplement volunteer work.
</p>
